--- ghsrc/gmod-chttp/README.md	1970-01-01 00:00:00.000000000 +0000
+++ gmod-chttp-proxy-fork/README.md	2026-04-09 21:12:16.879567029 +0000
@@ -0,0 +1,37 @@
+# gmod-chttp proxy patchset
+
+This patchset adds **per-request proxy settings** to `gmod-chttp`, so Lua code can set:
+
+- `proxy`
+- `proxy_userpwd` or `proxy_username` + `proxy_password`
+- `proxy_type` (`http`, `https`, `socks4`, `socks4a`, `socks5`, `socks5h`)
+- `proxy_auth` (`basic`, `digest`, `ntlm`, `any`, `anysafe`)
+
+## Intended flow
+
+`Server -> HTTP proxy / VPN -> Discord / Telegram`
+
+## Why this patch exists
+
+Stock `gmod-chttp` is already a drop-in replacement for Garry's Mod `HTTP()` and it lets the `OnCHTTPRequest` hook edit the outgoing `HTTPRequest` structure before dispatch.
+This patch extends the structure so the hook can inject proxy settings without changing every addon call site.
+
+## Example Lua usage
+
+```lua
+HTTP({
+    url = "https://discord.com/api/v10/gateway",
+    method = "GET",
+    proxy = "http://127.0.0.1:10809",
+    proxy_username = "user",
+    proxy_password = "pass",
+    proxy_type = "http",
+    proxy_auth = "any",
+    success = function(code, body, headers) print(code, body) end,
+    failed = function(err) print(err) end,
+})
+```
+
+## Hook-based usage
+
+See `filter/proxy.lua`. With the hook approach, you can override `HTTP = CHTTP` and let the hook route only selected domains through the proxy.
